SIMPLE: wildfire
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wildfire
<hw>Wild"fire</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
composition of inflammable materials, which, kindled, is very hard to
quench; Greek fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brimstone, pitch, <qex>wildfire</qex> . . . burn cruelly, and hard
to quench.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An old name for
erysipelas.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A disease of sheep, attended with
inflammation of the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sort of lightning unaccompanied by thunder.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wildgrave</ent>⟦br⟧
